Hi,

In the format (LoggingEvent) method, the following piece of code exists:

    Throwable t = event.throwable; // JVM is a stack machine
    if(t != null) {
      sbuf.append("\r\n<tr><td colspan=\"7\">");
      sbuf.append(getThrowableAsHTML(t));
      sbuf.append("</td></tr>");
    }

However, this is a problem if the LoggingEvent has no Throwable object, and has dumped the stacktrace in throwableInformation (normally when the event is serialised to be passed through a stream). Changing it is straight forward enough.

BTW, in the Severity section of the bug report, there's both a "Normal" and a "normal" field. :)

Allan.
